import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['stars'] = pd.to_numeric(data['stars'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='stars', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['stars'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["stars"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of stars for the repositories?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
